review_blob: Despite being in New Mexico, where most green bottles become skunked in the display case, this one seems to have been boxed until recently.  Great caramel and dark fruit in the aroma, little hops to muddle it, well-balanced sweetness.  Pours sweet-tea brown with a slight off-white head which held for less than a minute.  No lacing, but hey! I dont think this is that kind of beer.  For me, this bottle delivered a beautiful shadow of an afternoon in Munich.
